# Haven Product Context

Before any product, design, or engineering work on Haven, read these documents:

1. [HAVEN_MANIFESTO.md](HAVEN_MANIFESTO.md) — why Haven exists (product soul)
2. [HAVEN_HOME_EXPERIENCE.md](HAVEN_HOME_EXPERIENCE.md) — daily financial ritual on Home
3. [HAVEN_FINANCIAL_PULSE.md](HAVEN_FINANCIAL_PULSE.md) — Check-In interaction (Home Experience v4)
4. [HAVEN_ARCHITECTURE.md](HAVEN_ARCHITECTURE.md) — engineering architecture
5. [HDL.md](HDL.md) — design language (discovered while building)
6. [PRODUCT_DECISIONS.md](PRODUCT_DECISIONS.md) — locked decisions with rationale

## Workflow

1. Understand the problem.
2. Propose solutions.
3. Explain trade-offs.
4. Recommend one option.
5. Once locked, do not revisit without compelling reason.

## Rules

- Check PRODUCT_DECISIONS.md before proposing changes to locked decisions.
- Update HDL for validated design patterns — not the manifesto.
- Log new locked decisions in PRODUCT_DECISIONS.md with date and rationale.
- Disagree when necessary. Do not agree to be polite.
- Refer to people as "members," not "users."
- No hardcoded design values — use Haven design tokens.
- Consistency is more important than novelty.
